data.title: Border Humanity Project - Category - Why We Welcome
data.description: The ACLU Border Humanity Project is a proud member of the #WelcomeWithDignity Campaign, which has been working with groups on the ground receiving migrants and people seeking asylum. As part of a political stunt, the governors of TX, AZ, and FL sent some people seeking safety in the U.S. to places where they have no family or friends to welcome them. The governors' intent was clear - to advance their hateful political goals, inflame public opinion and dehumanize people seeking asylum.
